  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="hero">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Recruiter-ready QA demo</p>
        <h1>CertGate public QA showcase</h1>
        <p>
          Live snapshot of the automated gating run: pytest layers, Great Expectations checkpoints,
          and structured release exports. Every workflow refresh pushes a clickable page for the hiring
          team to inspect.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <a class="demo-link" id="demo-link" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Live demo link</a>
        <p class="hero-meta" id="demo-url">Loading link...</p>
      </div>
    </header>
    <main>
      <section class="status-panel">
        <article class="card status-card">
          <span class="status-pill" id="status-pill" data-status="loading">Loading...</span>
          <h2 id="status-text">Fetching validation data...</h2>
          <p id="status-timestamp"></p>
          <p id="status-reason"></p>
          <ul id="fail-list"><li>Waiting for the latest release decision.</li></ul>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <p class="section-title">Validation coverage</p>
          <div class="stats-grid">
            <div class="stat">
              <p class="stat-label">Rules evaluated</p>
              <p class="stat-value" id="rule-count">—</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <p class="stat-label">Failures</p>
              <p class="stat-value" id="failed-count">—</p>
            </div>
            <div class="stat">
              <p class="stat-label">Generated</p>
              <p class="stat-value" id="generated-at">—</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>
      <section class="overview card">
        <p class="section-title">Project overview</p>
        <p>
          CertGate combines schema and business-rule automation to guard releases for the candidate,
          examination, and certification feeds. Pytest layers exercise every helper and regression
          scenario, while Great Expectations keeps data docs and checkpoints live for recruiters.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section class="rule-categories">
        <article class="rule-card">
          <h3>Schema &amp; completeness</h3>
          <p>Ensure required columns, dtypes, and unique identifiers before a batch ever lands in production.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rule-card">
          <h3>Consistency &amp; integrity</h3>
          <p>Candidate joins, pass/fail status mappings, and certification uniqueness guard the business logic.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="rule-card">
          <h3>Freshness &amp; timeliness</h3>
          <p>Metadata and timestamps verify that data arrives within the 24-hour window or flags a warning.</p>
        </article>
      </section>
